        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any paywall trigger or upgrade prompt" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always show paywalls after the user has experienced real value (the 'aha moment'), never before. The upgrade should feel like a natural next step, not an interruption." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Asking before value is delivered is the #1 conversion killer — users who haven't felt the product's worth will never convert." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_170904ab a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing paywall screen content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Demonstrate the value of paid features visually (previews, screenshots, before/after) rather than just listing them. Make the upgrade feel tangible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users need to feel what they're missing, not just read about it. Visual proof drives higher conversion than feature lists." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_26f69646 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring paywall display rules and frequency" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Limit paywall frequency: enforce per-session caps and use cool-down periods measured in days (not hours) after user dismissal. Never re-show after dismissal within the same session." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Too-frequent prompts create annoyance, reducing both conversion likelihood and user engagement." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_3a54f624 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any upgrade screen or modal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Provide a clear escape hatch on every paywall ('Not now', 'Continue with Free', 'Maybe Later'). Never block users from continuing their current workflow." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Respecting the user's choice to decline maintains trust and leaves the door open for future conversion attempts." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_668f2b89 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before providing any paywall recommendations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check for `.agents/product-marketing-context.md` (or `.claude/product-marketing-context.md` in older setups) and read it before asking questions. Only ask for information not already covered in the context document." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Product marketing context contains pricing model, feature tiering, and positioning data essential for paywall design." .

oc:kn_83f96adc a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing when and how to display upgrade prompts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Four trigger point types cover most upgrade moments: (1) Feature Gates — user clicks a paid-only feature, (2) Usage Limits — user hits a free tier threshold, (3) Trial Expiration — trial is ending with warnings at 7/3/1 days, (4) Time-Based Prompts — after X days of sustained free use." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each trigger type has a different user emotional state and requires tailored messaging to convert effectively." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_995fa740 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When measuring paywall performance and A/B test results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Track these metrics to evaluate paywall effectiveness: paywall impression rate, click-through to upgrade, completion rate, revenue per user, and churn rate post-upgrade." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These metrics form a complete funnel view from impression to revenue retention, enabling data-driven optimization." .

oc:kn_a3eeb509 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any upgrade screen or modal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use dark patterns: hiding the close button, confusing plan selection, guilt-trip copy, or trapping users in upgrade flows. Always provide a clear escape hatch." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dark patterns may boost short-term conversion but destroy long-term trust, increase churn, and damage brand reputation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b181fcaa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When working on any paywall or upgrade screen task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Check for product-marketing-context.md and load it. 2. Identify upgrade context (freemium→paid, trial→paid, tier upgrade, feature upsell, usage limit). 3. Map user journey to find value moments and trigger points. 4. Select paywall type (feature lock, usage limit, trial expiration). 5. Apply 7-component paywall framework (headline, value demo, feature comparison, pricing, social proof, CTA, escape hatch). 6. Optimize upgrade flow (minimize steps, pre-fill info, keep in-context). 7. Plan A/B tests for trigger timing, copy, layout, and pricing presentation." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_c46a4501 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting paywall display triggers and timing rules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not show upgrade prompts during onboarding (too early), when users are mid-task/flow, or repeatedly after dismissal. These are conversion killers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Interrupting core user flows destroys trust and activation. Users who feel ambushed will resent the product, not upgrade." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

